Close to 900 million people travel internationally each year and estimates suggest that up to 7% of travelers are children. 1-3 Consequently, upwards of 60 million children may travel internationally each year. Annually up to 8% of travelers to the developing regions of the world are ill enough to seek medical healthcare while abroad or upon returning home. 4,5 Although travel can expose children to some risks, the benefits are many. Therefore, a careful pretravel evaluation to provide appropriate guidance and preparation is critical to protect pediatric travelers and their families and allow them to enjoy their time abroad. 